  "prompt": "Does every student at iiser get fellowship?",
  "response": "At the Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research (IISERs), all students admitted to the BS-MS dual degree program are eligible for a monthly fellowship. However, the continuation of the fellowship is subject to certain conditions:\n\n1. **Academic Performance**: Students must maintain a minimum Cumulative Grade Point Average (CGPA) to be eligible for the fellowship. This threshold can vary between different IISERs but is generally around 6.0 to 7.0 on a 10-point scale.\n\n2. **Attendance and Conduct**: Students are expected to maintain good attendance and adhere to the institute's code of conduct. Violations can lead to the suspension or withdrawal of the fellowship.\n\n3. **Research and Internships**: Some IISERs might have additional criteria related to involvement in research projects or internships, especially in the later years of the program.\n\nIt's important to check the specific policies of the IISER to which you are applying or attending, as they might have slight variations in their fellowship policies.",
